        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:47PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking the leading edge of strong
winds associated with a cluster of thunderstorms. The winds were
along a line extending from 9 miles south of Lincolnton to 11 miles
southwest of Gastonia to 8 miles southeast of Gaffney. Movement was
southeast at 30 mph. Thunderstorms are likely to develop as these
winds push southeast.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph even without thunderstorms.
Stronger winds and hail will be possible when thunderstorms
develop.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Gastonia, Rock Hill, York, Chester, Southwest Charlotte, Kings
Mountain, Fort Mill, Pineville, and Bessemer City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Severe thunderstorms producing damaging winds may develop, so be
certain to monitor local radio stations and available television
stations for additional information and possible warnings from the
National Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
the Piedmont of North Carolina...and Upstate South Carolina.</instruction>
